text.text:
A purrfect way to spend a cloudy Sunday afternoon! Make a reservation in advance to make the most out of this visit, and be sure to pop by the cafe before entering the cat room at least 10 minutes before you enter the room of adorable and soft cats to pet and play with! Whether you’re enjoying a nice cold or hot beverage with your loved ones, this is the most clean cat facility I’ve ever been to!
Easy access to free parking across the street and a calming atmosphere for everyone.
I would highly recommend checking this and other cat cafes who are either looking to
Adopt or simply to hang out with these incredibly happy felines in a clean and friendly atmosphere!

This was hands down the best experience ever. Our beloved cat of 14 years passed away last year and we were ready to welcome some new cats into our family. The setup is so calming for the cats, lots of places to sleep or hide or play. Music going. Not too many people in there at a time to overwhelm them.

We left with two (not the same litter) and they have bonded really well. Couldn’t be  happier !

If I could give them 100 stars I would! This cat cafe is incredible because you are hanging out with adoptable shelter cats. The cats are adorable, and so much fun. I loved every second of it! This was a huge dose of serotonin for me, and I am hopeful every single one of the cats finds their furever home soon! Highly recommend!

This was our second trip to Purrfect Day Cafe.  Both visits were for ~10 year old girl birthday parties.  I was skeptical at first, but this is an absolutely brilliant concept.
The dedicated “petting room” is full of 10ish kittens.  They are just at the age of being spayed/neutered. It’s a great way to acclimate the cats to people.  All cats are available for adoption.
My only complaint is the same thing as any Bardstown Road business.  Parking is horrible.
I don’t know how one-off visits actually work,  but I highly recommend checking this place out if you have the chance.

This is the most adorable coffee shop I’ve ever been to, a pretty cool concept. You can go visit the cafe anytime but might need a reservation to see the cats/kittens depending on the day of the week.
Kittens galore, swag, great coffee drinks, and don’t even get me started on the adoptions eeekkk! Once you’ve played with the kittens, you have the opportunity to take one or more home. It’s a very easy process and the kittens have already been fixed and vaccinated so you don’t even have to stop at the vet on the way home.

Check out their booking page, they have events that are great for girls and date nights. You can’t go wrong with the Purrfect Day Cat Cafe.

*This is the first cafe in the nation to reach and pass 10,000 adoptions since opening its doors. There’s magic in the Highlands, don’t miss out.

Absolutely amazing!! Whenever I visit a new city, I try to look for kitty cafes. Purrfect Day exceeded my expectations. The staff were so friendly and welcoming & the stars of the show (the 2-3 month old kittens) were soooooo cute and playful and cuddly. The room was clean, had plenty of toys and sleeping nooks for the kitties, was a great size and wasn’t overcrowded. I wish I could’ve stayed all night!

I loved visiting Lucky Cat Cafe. There were about 12 cats when I visited and they were all so friendly. The cats were obviously very well taken care of and the establishment was very clean. I loved visiting with the cats and petting them all. The staff was very friendly and helpful. They have a cute little gift shop with great gifts for cat lovers.

Cute, older home turned into a non-profit cat lounge. The employees were all very kind and welcoming and the cats seemed incredibly well cared for. There's not much parking, and it does get a bit cramped inside when there's a lot of people but overall, it was definitely worth the visit!

A charming environment to visit with cats and meet new people. It's such a nice, clean, calm place where you can really play and snuggle each cat.we loved it and will be bringing all our out of town friends and family!

Finally got to try this place and it was delicious! Sadly, they are only open until 2pm so I’ve never been able to get there before now. Wish they’d expand the hours on the weekends at least. But I’ll definitely try to go back. It was very tasty and reasonably priced

I like this place.  Very good breakfast.  They serve it with plastic utensils and foam plates but that’s not an issue for me.  The food is very good.  It’s a nice place with friendly service.  Do I love eating off plastic and foam? No.  But the food and atmosphere is good enough that I really don’t care.  The world is different after COVID so I don’t mind.  I will be back.  And I’ll get it to-go on occasion.
The pumpkin Gouda soup was delicious!  Mom had bean soup and said it was perfectly seasoned, delicious as well.  This was my first time stopping in but won’t be the last.

cafes.name: Central Purrk Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 401 Outlet Center Dr #260, Georgetown, KY 40324, USA

text.text: We visited on a Saturday morning for a Yoga with Cats event. For $20, we received a 45 minute yoga session, 15 minutes of Cat Lounge time, and a small drink. I chose the vanilla iced coffee, and it was delicious! The Cat Lounge area was well maintained, and the cats appeared to be very content. We enjoyed using the various toy options available to play with the cats, and they seemed to have a lot of fun with them. Definitely recommend checking this place out and booking ahead if you want to go inside the Cat Lounge (or to visit for an event). Maybe you’ll even find a furry friend to take home!

Wonderful place! Cats are clearly well taken care of. Everyone is so sweet! Jennifer was the bubbliest thing ever. Michaella made great coffee with a big smile. Kayleigh is so much fun to sit and laugh with. Great place guys. Thank you and I'll be back!
I love going here! The service is great, and the kitties are so well taken care of! I'm so happy to have a place like this in our community!

cafes.name: Lucy & Oscar's Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 1201 N Dixie Hwy Suite 104A, Elizabethtown, KY 42701, USA

text.text: Very lovely place! The cats are sweet and the staff was friendly.

cafes.name: Tortitude Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 2420 New Holt Rd, Paducah, KY 42001, USA

text.text: Visiting Tortitude Cat Cafe was even more wonderful than I expected.  They offer a fun and cozy atmosphere, friendly staff, and adorable cats. Spending time with the cats and kittens not only gives you a warm and fuzzy feeling, but helps play a crucial role in socializing them, and helping them to be adopted into loving homes. Every cat was SO cute and friendly.   The cost,  which is quite reasonable, contributes to something so much bigger, which is the wonderful mission of caring for and finding homes for abandoned cats. Your visit truly makes a difference. This was a great birthday experience to share with daughter.  Highly recommend!!

What a great place! The climbing wall and cat wheel are the purrfect tips for cat adopters on how to make their own home a cat paradise. These kitties are so lucky to be here and we had a wonderful time meeting them. Fantastic and attentive staff! Dream job 😻

If you love cats, come in for a visit. Either to just spend 30 mins($7 per person) with all the cats or adopt a fur baby. They have baked goods(kitty cookies when we were there) & coffee. Other human treats if those ain't your thing. Pretty spacious spot for the cats to run & play. & for their human visitors to sit. If you're a cat person, I'd suggest paying em a visit. It's a good thing these people have brought to Paducah. Let's support it. My wife & I will definitely be back.
